3. Prepare phase

  Data stored.

We are using data called FiBit Fitness. The data stored in Kaggle and Mobius is the owner of this data.

 The privacy, license, and accessibility of the data.

This dataset was generated by respondents to a distributed survey via Amazon Mechanical Turk between 03.12.2016-05.12.2016. Thirty-three eligible Fitbit users consented to the submission of personal tracker data, including minute-level output for physical activity, heart rate, and sleep monitoring.
By checking the metadata we can confirm that the data is for public use, and the owner gives us access to analyze it and share our work.

Information about the data.

The data has 18 CSV files and it contains thirty-three participants. Each document represents different quantitative data tracked by Fitbit.
As I can see, the data is not recently collected; the last update was two years ago.
Each user has a unique Id and the survey has been tracking users’ activity for 31 days 





3.4 Organizing the data.
The data are presented in large format because each subject has information in multiple rows. I have made some changes using Excel to organize the columns, make sure there are no duplicates, take a look at the filter to see if there is any suspiciousness with the data, and adjust the date to be consistent, moreover, I have also named and separated the files into folders as CSV to upload it to SQL. I will use three files which will be the tables( Active, Sleep, and Steps)
Regarding the credibility of the data, it is also considered sample bias data since it’s collected from just thirty-three people without including enough people in the survey and for a short amount of time.



4. Process and analyze phase

programs.
I will work on SQL because I want to focus more on it, and I will use Tableau to create data visualization.
Data integrity.
Although the data was collected from only thirty-three people it still lacks integrity because many participants didn’t provide their information for the 31 days and some fields were left blank which led to uncompleted and inconsistent data.

Working on the data
I will create a database and then create a table for each file. After I finished we can see the schema, details, and preview of the files.
The files that I have uploaded are Activity, Steps, and Sleep.

Now we can start cleaning and analyzing the data.

